<task id="024" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-16 Playbook FK Fix — Wire `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` Node → `SUM-CHAT@v1` Action (Pillar 4)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>011</dependencies>
    <blocks>025</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, seed, data-fix, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Dataverse data fix (no `.cs`); idempotent FK update on existing rows; validates at startup; gates Pillar 4 orchestrator refactor.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A-G3</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent data fix; parallel with 020 (facade); both unblocked by 011.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Fix the broken Foreign Key in the `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` playbook's node:
    wire its action FK to `SUM-CHAT@v1`. The FK currently bypasses the chain (per R5
    closeout limitation acknowledged in Pillar 4), which is why
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` loads the action by alternate key. After this fix, the
    full chain `playbook → node → action` is populated and the orchestrator (task 025)
    can route through `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync` without the alternate-key
    bypass.

    Critical-path context: this single Dataverse data fix closes a long-standing R5
    architectural debt. Task 025 (orchestrator refactor) consumes this fix.

    Implementation: write an idempotent migration script that (a) verifies the
    `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` playbook exists; (b) verifies the `SUM-CHAT@v1`
    action exists; (c) updates the node's action-FK column to point at `SUM-CHAT@v1`;
    (d) verifies the FK chain validates at BFF startup (i.e., no startup error from
    `PlaybookExecutionEngine` initial validation pass).

    NFR-08 binding: this task does NOT modify any of the 11 production node executors.
    It's a pure data fix on existing rows.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Dataverse engineer + AI platform familiarity. Familiar with playbook canvas
    schema (playbook → nodes → action FK) and the BFF's startup FK-validation pass.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `summarize-document-for-chat@v1`'s node FK points at `SUM-CHAT@v1` action. FK chain
    validates at BFF startup (no error log). Migration script is idempotent (re-runs
    are no-ops). Acceptance criteria green.
  </goal>

