  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD — Dataverse data fix; no `.cs`".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 011 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Read R5 lessons-learned `Gap B` section on the playbook FK bypass.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Verify Current State">
      Query Dataverse: confirm `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` playbook exists; confirm `SUM-CHAT@v1` action exists; capture current FK value of the playbook's node.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author Idempotent Migration Script">
      Write PowerShell / Web API script: (a) idempotent check (current FK already = `SUM-CHAT@v1` → no-op); (b) else update node's action FK. Include rollback note: original FK captured in script comment for manual reversal if needed.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="🛑 Confirmation Gate — Data Fix Deployment">
      PAUSE per project CLAUDE.md §Confirmation Triggers (production Dataverse data change). Present current FK + planned new FK + idempotency check; request approval.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Deploy Data Fix to Spaarke Dev">
      Run script. Verify FK now points at `SUM-CHAT@v1`.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Startup FK Validation">
      Restart BFF (or invoke startup validation pass). Confirm: no FK-validation error logs for `summarize-document-for-chat@v1`.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Idempotency">
      Re-run script; confirm: no-op; no data destruction.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk each criterion; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 024 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report. Note BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
    </step>
  </steps>

